verbose_text: After 8 weeks, by electrostimulating of the cavernous nerve, maximal intracavernous pressure (MICP), mean arterial pressure (MAP), ICP / MAP, Tmax (the time of stimulating MICP happened), cavernosal filling rate (CFR) were measured with radioimmunoassay to evaluate the erectile function of rats; the levels of plasma testosterone (T) were measured with radioimmunoassay, the activity of superoxide dismutase (SOD), MDA, NOS, from cavernosal tissue homogenate was measured.
